               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) I) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus” (fols.1ra-119v) 
 I-1)
                     Introduction (fols. 1ra-2vb, 67ra-68rb l.6), incomplete [the middle part of the
                     text is in MGM-008a]
 - On John the Evangelist as the author of the book
                     (fol. 1ra-vb) 
 - Story of the family of Adam (fols. 2ra-vb, 67ra-68rb l.6)
                     
 I-2) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus”: 47 miracles (fols. 3ra-119vb).
                     I) Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus” (fols.1ra-119rb) 
 I-1) Introduction
                     (fols. 1ra-2vb, 67ra-68rb; some fols missing between fols. 1 and 2) 
 - On
                     John the Evangelist as the author of the book (fols. 1ra-1vb; incomplete)
                     - Story of the family of Adam (fols. 2ra-2vb, 67ra-68rb; incomplete)
 I-2)
                     Taʾammǝra ʾIyasus “Miracles of Jesus”: 47 miracles (fols. 3ra-119rb)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The miracles are numbered; the scribe began the numbering from Story of
                        the family of Adam (Text I-1; since the beginning of this section is
                        missing, the first number is 3) and continued up to the last miracle. The
                        first miracle proper has the number 4.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
